1
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,760
Are you a pirate?

2
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:55,800
Yep!

3
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:59,890
So why did you fire a cannonball
at our restaurant again?

4
00:01:59,890 --> 00:02:01,600
That was an accident!

5
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,600
A stray shot in self-defense!

6
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,940
A what, now...?

7
00:02:05,940 --> 00:02:09,480
Whatever. Just don't try
any funny business here.

8
00:02:09,820 --> 00:02:13,570
The proprietor was once a cook
on an infamous pirate crew.

9
00:02:14,660 --> 00:02:16,780
So the boss man was a pirate!

10
00:02:17,450 --> 00:02:22,330
This restaurant is
that old fart's treasure.

11
00:02:22,830 --> 00:02:29,960
And the cooks who admire and flock
to him are hotheaded pirate types.

12
00:02:30,590 --> 00:02:35,550
Well, they're a perfect fit
for a place that pirates frequent.

13
00:02:35,550 --> 00:02:39,010
This restaurant is pretty wild.

14
00:02:39,010 --> 00:02:42,020
Yeah, that's the norm here.

15
00:02:42,020 --> 00:02:46,810
Some people come here just to see
the cooks and pirates going at it.

16
00:02:47,230 --> 00:02:52,610
But it freaks out the waiters,
so all of them quit.

17
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:57,240
I see... So that's why the boss man
wants me to work here for a year.

18
00:02:57,990 --> 00:03:00,030
Hey, join our crew.

19
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:01,790
I refuse.

20
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:05,960
I've got my reasons for staying here.

21
00:03:06,290 --> 00:03:06,960
No!

22
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:07,830
I refuse!

23
00:03:08,420 --> 00:03:09,170
Say what?!

24
00:03:09,710 --> 00:03:12,840
I refuse your refusal!

25
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:16,340
You're a good cook,
so let's be pirates together.

26
00:03:16,970 --> 00:03:19,550
H-Hey! You haven't heard my reason!

27
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:20,810
Okay, what's the reason?

28
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:22,720
None of your business!

29
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:25,600
You just told me to listen!

30
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:29,940
I mean you should
respect my damn decision!

31
00:03:29,940 --> 00:03:32,940
I'll fillet you like a salmon,
you dirty straw-hat bastard!

32
00:03:32,940 --> 00:03:33,860
What'd you say?!

33
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:37,360
Make fun of this hat, and I'll
knock you into next week, you jerk!

34
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:40,200
Sorry to interrupt...

35
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,080
– What?!
– What?!

36
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:45,120
I'm Gin of the Krieg Pirates.

37
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,080
You're a pirate too, right?

38
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:49,210
What's your goal?

39
00:03:49,210 --> 00:03:51,590
I'm after the One Piece.

40
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:53,500
I'm going to the Grand Line.

41
00:03:57,340 --> 00:04:02,850
Since you're looking for a cook,
you must not have much of a crew yet.

42
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:04,720
Yep. He's our fifth member.

43
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,850
Why are you counting me?!

44
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:10,980
You seem like a nice guy,
so let me warn you.

45
00:04:10,980 --> 00:04:13,480
Give up on going to the Grand Line.

46
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:17,110
You're still young.
No need to rush into things.

47
00:04:17,110 --> 00:04:20,620
The Grand Line is just a fraction
of the world's oceans anyway.

48
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:24,410
There are much safer waters
out there for a pirate.

49
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:26,950
Oh, really?

50
00:04:27,330 --> 00:04:29,960
Do you know a lot
about the Grand Line?

51
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,330
No...

52
00:04:31,330 --> 00:04:34,500
I don't know anything...
I don't understand anything about it...

53
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:36,760
Which is exactly why it terrifies me...

54
00:04:38,010 --> 00:04:42,010
For one of Krieg's men,
you sure sound like a wimp.

55
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:43,890
Who's Krieg?

56
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,270
Hors d'oeuvres for table three!

57
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:55,440
Serve it yourself.

58
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:57,110
We don't have any waiters.

59
00:04:59,450 --> 00:05:01,360
Do you think we'll be okay, Patty?

60
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,110
Say what?

61
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:06,740
I hear that guy you beat up
in the restaurant earlier

62
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:09,870
is one of the Krieg Pirates.

63
00:05:09,870 --> 00:05:12,580
Yeah, you heard correctly.

64
00:05:12,580 --> 00:05:18,210
Don Krieg's the most powerful,
vile pirate in these waters.

65
00:05:18,210 --> 00:05:19,340
That's right.

66
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:28,390
After all, he's the don of an armada,
commanding fifty captains,

67
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:33,400
each helming their own pirate ship.

68
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:36,940
He's nothing short of a monster...

69
00:05:36,940 --> 00:05:38,860
So, what's the big deal?

70
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:44,660
I heard that his forces consist
of more than 5,000 pirates.

71
00:05:46,450 --> 00:05:53,710
If that guy from earlier tells
Don Krieg how we mistreated him,

72
00:05:54,080 --> 00:06:00,840
everyone here would be crushed like ants
under a parade of stampeding elephants.

73
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:02,720
Oh, yeah...?

74
00:06:03,050 --> 00:06:08,430
So you're saying I should've
just served the guy?

75
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:12,140
That'd be rude
to the actual customers!

76
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:20,940
I'd rather not ruin the reputation of the
fighting cooks of the Sea Restaurant, Baratie!

77
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:26,990
How many pirates do you
think we've chased off?

78
00:06:26,990 --> 00:06:29,450
If you're that scared, just quit!

79
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:30,620
How could you say that?!

80
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:34,830
Y'know, that big mouth of yours
is the reason all the waiters left!

81
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:38,380
Patty, this means it's
your fault we're short-staffed!

82
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:43,720
Those wimps were
useless from the start!

83
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:45,380
Go for it!

84
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:46,590
Carne, take him out!

85
00:06:46,590 --> 00:06:48,140
Clobber him, Patty!

86
00:06:49,220 --> 00:06:50,970
Hey, you bunch of meatheads!

87
00:06:50,970 --> 00:06:52,980
Get back to work!

88
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:54,940
– Yes, Chef Zeff!
– Yes, Chef Zeff!

89
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,860
So long, then...

90
00:06:57,860 --> 00:07:00,730
But I'm still going to the Grand Line.

91
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:01,650
Sure...

92
00:07:01,650 --> 00:07:03,400
Do what you like.

93
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:07,110
A passerby like myself has
no right to try and stop you.

94
00:07:07,110 --> 00:07:10,330
Just thought I'd warn you.

95
00:07:10,330 --> 00:07:12,370
And Sanji...

96
00:07:12,370 --> 00:07:14,210
thank you so much!

97
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:16,710
I owe you my life.

98
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:19,540
That meal was incredibly delicious.

99
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,500
Could I come back for more?

100
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,420
Come back any time!

101
00:07:23,420 --> 00:07:26,260
Hey, Cabin Boy!

102
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:27,470
Boss Man!

103
00:07:27,470 --> 00:07:29,140
There you are!

104
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:35,020
Go, Gin.

105
00:07:36,230 --> 00:07:37,650
Sorry.

106
00:07:37,650 --> 00:07:41,400
You're gonna get in trouble for
giving me a free meal, aren't you?

107
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:43,480
Well...

108
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:56,210
No proof, no trouble.

109
00:08:02,630 --> 00:08:04,840
Don't get caught next time, Gin!

110
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:06,670
Thank you, Sanji!

111
00:08:06,670 --> 00:08:09,300
I'll never forget your kindness!

112
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,390
Sanji! Cabin Boy!

113
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:13,390
Get back to work already!

114
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:16,810
Hey, table three is ready!

115
00:08:20,270 --> 00:08:21,400
I'm Luffy!

116
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,230
I'm your new cabin boy.

117
00:08:23,230 --> 00:08:24,940
Nice to meet you!

118
00:08:39,420 --> 00:08:41,710
Where's table six's dessert?

119
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:45,300
Hey, who's responsible
for that order?!

120
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:46,800
Isn't it you?!

121
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,180
I'm too busy right now!

122
00:08:49,180 --> 00:08:50,760
Get your head on straight!

123
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:52,970
Wanna say that again to my fists?!

124
00:08:55,220 --> 00:08:59,640
– Be useful and wash the dishes, Cabin Boy!
– Be useful and wash the dishes, Cabin Boy!

125
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,190
Where's Sanji?

126
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:03,900
Flirting in the dining room.

127
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:05,150
Again?!

128
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:10,360
I'm annoyed enough as it is
having him as the sous chef.

129
00:09:10,740 --> 00:09:12,030
Deal with it.

130
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:14,830
He's been here the longest.

131
00:09:15,330 --> 00:09:20,920
Do you know why he stays here,
when he doesn't get along with the owner?

132
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:23,460
He wants to be head chef someday.

133
00:09:23,460 --> 00:09:25,420
You'd have to be blind to miss it.

134
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:32,090
Hey, Cabin Boy!

135
00:09:32,090 --> 00:09:35,470
How many dishes
have you broken so far?!

136
00:09:35,470 --> 00:09:38,140
Oh, sorry. I forgot to count.

137
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:41,980
That's not what I meant!
Apologize for breaking them!

138
00:09:41,980 --> 00:09:45,110
Forget about washing dishes.
Go clean over there!

139
00:09:45,110 --> 00:09:46,480
Okay, leave it to me!

140
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:50,440
Don't pick at the plates!

141
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:53,070
That's an entrée!

142
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:55,490
Oh, don't worry about it!

143
00:09:55,490 --> 00:09:57,410
Ouch!

144
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:03,000
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

145
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,000
– Just get out of the kitchen!
– Just get out of the kitchen!

146
00:10:03,460 --> 00:10:05,960
Go and take orders, okay?

147
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:10,300
Ask customers what they want to eat!
You can do that much, right?!

148
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,590
Yep.

149
00:10:11,590 --> 00:10:13,880
Chores sure are hard.

150
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,430
Koby must've been miserable.

151
00:10:15,430 --> 00:10:17,470
Hey, Cabin Boy!

152
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:19,390
You guys...

153
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:21,810
I heard you have to work
here for a year.

154
00:10:21,810 --> 00:10:23,890
Can we change the ship's flag?

155
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:28,650
Wh-Wh-Why are you guys...
eating yummy food without me?!

156
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:30,070
That's just cruel!

157
00:10:30,070 --> 00:10:32,820
There's no reason
we shouldn't be, right guys?

158
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:34,780
Take this!

159
00:10:35,990 --> 00:10:37,240
Y-Yeah, no reason...

160
00:10:38,620 --> 00:10:41,910
Man, the food sure is good here.

161
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:44,830
Well...

162
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:47,670
I feel bad for you, but...

163
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:50,710
you drink it!

164
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,050
I can't believe you did that!

165
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:57,890
I can't believe you did that!

166
00:10:57,890 --> 00:11:00,010
So gross! So gross!

167
00:10:57,510 --> 00:11:00,010
My sides hurt from laughing!

168
00:11:07,230 --> 00:11:09,190
What a noisy bunch...

169
00:11:09,190 --> 00:11:09,980
Are they...

170
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,650
his crewmates?

171
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:18,410
Pour it yourself.

172
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,950
Oh, dear ocean,

173
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:23,250
I thank you for today's encounter!

174
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,040
– What?!
– What?!

175
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:26,120
Oh, love...

176
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,500
I can't bear this hardship.

177
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:29,960
Go ahead and laugh at me.

178
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:35,590
I would readily be a lowly pirate
—or perhaps even a devil—

179
00:11:35,590 --> 00:11:36,720
to be by your side!

180
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:41,060
However, how tragic it is!

181
00:11:41,060 --> 00:11:44,270
The obstacle separating us
is far too great!

182
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:47,690
I'm that obstacle, right...

183
00:11:47,690 --> 00:11:48,980
Sanji?

184
00:11:48,980 --> 00:11:50,560
The old fart...!

185
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:55,440
This is a good opportunity.
Why don't you join their pirate crew?

186
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:58,740
I don't need you here anymore!

187
00:12:14,210 --> 00:12:15,670
I see...

188
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:21,550
That cook saved your life,
and you made it back here.

189
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:25,020
Is that what you're saying, Gin?

190
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,980
Y-Yes...

191
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:28,980
B-But...

192
00:12:29,350 --> 00:12:33,230
I didn't know our flagship
was in such bad shape...

193
00:12:33,230 --> 00:12:34,650
Don Krieg!

194
00:12:34,650 --> 00:12:36,070
What?

195
00:12:38,610 --> 00:12:39,910
I'll take you there,

196
00:12:39,910 --> 00:12:42,660
to the Sea Restaurant Baratie.

197
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:48,830
Hey, you old fart.

198
00:12:48,830 --> 00:12:51,130
I'm the sous chef here.

199
00:12:51,130 --> 00:12:53,630
What do you mean
you don't need me?!

200
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:56,010
You always cause problems
with the customers.

201
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:59,260
You flare your nostrils
the second you see a lady.

202
00:12:59,260 --> 00:13:01,340
Factor in your lousy cooking,

203
00:13:01,340 --> 00:13:04,140
and you're just dead weight
to this restaurant.

204
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:05,640
That's why I don't need you.

205
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:07,470
Come again?

206
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:14,110
Besides, you're not exactly friends
with the other cooks.

207
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:20,030
So go be a pirate or whatever
and just leave this restaurant already!

208
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:22,660
What the hell...?

209
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:27,870
You're just gonna keep running
your mouth, huh, you old fart?

210
00:13:28,830 --> 00:13:33,420
The rest I could overlook, but I
won't let you insult my cooking!

211
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:37,840
I'll stay here and cook
no matter what you say!

212
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:39,630
I won't hear another word about it!

213
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:43,510
How dare you lay your hands
on the owner of this restaurant...

214
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:45,800
You damn eggplant!

215
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:50,100
Damn you...

216
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:54,860
No matter how hard
you try to kick me out,

217
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:58,440
I want to keep working here as a cook...

218
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:00,440
until you kick the bucket!

219
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,320
You'll be waiting a long time!

220
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,200
I'll live another 100 years.

221
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,410
The old fart just
has to have the last word...

222
00:14:06,410 --> 00:14:09,290
That's great! You got
permission to be a pirate!

223
00:14:09,290 --> 00:14:10,410
No way!

224
00:14:10,950 --> 00:14:12,500
Anyway...

225
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:14,290
Sorry about that.

226
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:17,460
By way of apology, accept this
fruit macédoine, my princess.

227
00:14:17,460 --> 00:14:19,670
Wow, thank you!

228
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:20,670
You're so kind.

229
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:21,420
It's nothing...

230
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:23,590
We don't get an apology?!

231
00:14:23,590 --> 00:14:26,220
I'm gonna sue for discrimination,
mister lover cook!

232
00:14:26,220 --> 00:14:28,930
I'm serving you tea, aren't I?

233
00:14:28,930 --> 00:14:30,720
Thank me for that, long nose.

234
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,230
Huh? You wanna fight?

235
00:14:32,230 --> 00:14:34,060
I won't go easy on you.

236
00:14:34,060 --> 00:14:35,650
Get him, Zoro!

237
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:37,190
Get him yourself.

238
00:14:37,190 --> 00:14:39,690
Stop! Please don't
fight because of me.

239
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:40,690
Yes, I'll stop.

240
00:14:40,690 --> 00:14:42,820
Who said it was because of you?!

241
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:44,110
By the way, you know...

242
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:44,910
Yes?

243
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:47,030
The food you have here is delicious...

244
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:49,410
but it's a bit on the expensive side...

245
00:14:49,410 --> 00:14:51,040
Oh, but it's free of charge.

246
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:52,540
Thank you!

247
00:14:53,580 --> 00:14:55,620
The rest of you have to pay.

248
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:55,620
Wha...?!

249
00:14:55,620 --> 00:14:57,840
You're too predictable.

250
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:02,300
What are you sitting around for?!

251
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:04,550
Bring out hot towels
for the customers!

252
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,550
Yes, sir.

253
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:42,170
Hourglasses flanking the skull
to intimidate all opposition!

254
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:44,300
That flag!

255
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:46,050
That flag...!

256
00:15:46,050 --> 00:15:49,680
It has to be the one who
conquered the East Blue...

257
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:52,640
Don Krieg!

258
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:07,570
Why...?!

259
00:16:07,570 --> 00:16:10,370
Why are the Krieg Pirates here?!

260
00:16:10,370 --> 00:16:13,330
You see, Patty?! They actually came!

261
00:16:13,330 --> 00:16:15,330
You're gonna get rid of them, right?!

262
00:16:15,330 --> 00:16:17,080
I-It can't be!

263
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:20,080
That guy is the head
of a 5,000-pirate armada!

264
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:23,340
Why would he come to avenge
just one of his men?!

265
00:16:23,340 --> 00:16:24,840
Well, it clearly can be!

266
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,670
He's really here!

267
00:16:26,670 --> 00:16:27,930
Hey, this is bad!

268
00:16:27,930 --> 00:16:30,180
Shouldn't we hightail it outta here?!

269
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:32,640
What a huge galleon!

270
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:41,860
That ship's humongous!

271
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:44,780
Maybe Gin came back to say thanks.

272
00:16:44,780 --> 00:16:47,280
I doubt that...

273
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:49,110
But this is strange...

274
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,110
Huh?

275
00:16:58,040 --> 00:16:59,290
H-Hey...

276
00:16:59,290 --> 00:17:00,960
Wh-What the...?

277
00:17:08,420 --> 00:17:11,390
Their ship sure is a mess...

278
00:17:11,390 --> 00:17:14,350
It doesn't look like damage
from cannon fire, either.

279
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:18,060
Actually, this damage
couldn't be man-made...

280
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:20,270
Did they sail through a waterspout?

281
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:24,190
Here he comes...

282
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:47,960
S-Sorry...

283
00:17:49,170 --> 00:17:52,930
Can I have some food and water?

284
00:17:53,470 --> 00:17:55,430
We have money...

285
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:57,850
tons of money...

286
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:01,270
What's he saying?!

287
00:18:01,270 --> 00:18:03,400
He's set aside pride and might.

288
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:08,280
Is he really that Don Krieg,
commodore of a grand pirate fleet?

289
00:18:08,280 --> 00:18:10,610
So he's hungry...

290
00:18:15,740 --> 00:18:17,410
C-Captain!

291
00:18:18,950 --> 00:18:20,450
Don Krieg!

292
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:23,500
P-Please!

293
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,210
Help our captain!

294
00:18:25,790 --> 00:18:27,590
He's going to starve!

295
00:18:28,130 --> 00:18:32,170
It's been days since his last meal,
so he'll die if he doesn't eat soon!

296
00:18:40,430 --> 00:18:42,270
Well, good!

297
00:18:42,270 --> 00:18:46,610
It's great to see the dreaded
Don Krieg in such a sorry state!

298
00:18:46,610 --> 00:18:48,440
I've got money this time.

299
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,860
We're customers!

300
00:18:49,860 --> 00:18:51,990
Don't be ridiculous!

301
00:18:51,990 --> 00:18:54,360
Hey, contact the Marines right away.

302
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,160
What?

303
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:58,870
He's on death's door!
This opportunity won't come again!

304
00:18:58,870 --> 00:19:00,490
Don't feed him anything!

305
00:19:00,490 --> 00:19:01,910
Just grab him!

306
00:19:02,620 --> 00:19:05,960
He's right! Who knows what
he'll do once he recuperates!

307
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:07,630
He's a villain.

308
00:19:07,630 --> 00:19:12,340
He deserves to starve
after everything he's done!

309
00:19:12,340 --> 00:19:16,470
No doubt he'll attack this restaurant
once he's back on his feet.

310
00:19:16,470 --> 00:19:19,100
Don't even give him a cup of water.

311
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:23,140
I won't try anything...

312
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:27,060
I won't try anything.

313
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:29,270
Once I've eaten,

314
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:31,610
I promise I'll leave quietly.

315
00:19:31,610 --> 00:19:35,280
So please... help... me...

316
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:38,160
Don Krieg, please stop!

317
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:40,530
Please stop begging!

318
00:19:40,530 --> 00:19:42,290
It's beneath you!

319
00:19:42,290 --> 00:19:45,040
Please don't do something
so disgraceful!

320
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:46,620
I promise...

321
00:19:47,370 --> 00:19:48,790
Please...

322
00:19:48,790 --> 00:19:52,090
I'll take leftovers or anything...

323
00:19:53,090 --> 00:19:55,130
Anything...

324
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:58,970
Don...

325
00:20:03,180 --> 00:20:05,180
Playing the sympathy card, huh?

326
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:07,270
Hey, move it, Patty.

327
00:20:13,150 --> 00:20:14,440
Whoa!

328
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:16,110
Sa...

329
00:20:16,860 --> 00:20:18,410
Sanji!

330
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:22,990
Here, Gin.

331
00:20:22,990 --> 00:20:24,580
He can eat this.

332
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:28,580
Sanji...

333
00:20:34,460 --> 00:20:35,510
Thank you!

334
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:49,350
Hey, Sanji! Take that food
away from him now!

335
00:20:49,810 --> 00:20:52,310
Do you realize
what kind of man he is?!

336
00:20:52,730 --> 00:20:55,820
He's the man who
conquered the East Blue,

337
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:57,570
Foul Play Krieg!

338
00:20:59,150 --> 00:21:03,410
He earned that name in prison
after he pretended to be a Marine

339
00:21:03,410 --> 00:21:07,500
and commandeered a ship
by killing its senior officer.

340
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:10,170
That's how he got started as a pirate.

341
00:21:11,460 --> 00:21:14,590
He would often raise the Marines'
flag when entering harbors

342
00:21:14,590 --> 00:21:16,760
to attack towns and passenger ships.

343
00:21:16,760 --> 00:21:19,930
He also attacked enemy vessels
under a white flag.

344
00:21:19,930 --> 00:21:22,140
He'll do anything to win.

345
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:24,510
That's how he got to where he is now!

346
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,970
What? That's playing dirty.

347
00:21:27,970 --> 00:21:31,060
His physical strength is
nothing to scoff at either.

348
00:21:31,060 --> 00:21:32,940
Leave once he's eaten?

349
00:21:32,940 --> 00:21:35,400
There's no way he'd do that!

350
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:40,240
The world would be a better place
if we let this demon bite the big one!

351
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:57,750
Sa...

352
00:21:57,750 --> 00:21:59,630
Sanji!

353
00:22:07,350 --> 00:22:08,100
This...

354
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,430
This isn't what we
agreed on, Don Krieg!

355
00:22:10,770 --> 00:22:14,690
You swore you wouldn't
hurt anybody here!

356
00:22:14,690 --> 00:22:16,440
And that man...

357
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:18,280
That man saved our lives–

358
00:22:22,820 --> 00:22:25,120
Yeah, that was delicious.

359
00:22:26,740 --> 00:22:28,370
I feel alive again.

360
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,840
H-Hey... Wh-Wha...?

361
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:49,350
Wh-What the hell
is going on in there?

362
00:22:49,350 --> 00:22:50,720
Let's go check it out.

363
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:52,560
What?! A-Are you serious?!

364
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:57,560
This is a good restaurant.

365
00:22:57,560 --> 00:22:59,690
I'll be taking this ship.

366
00:23:02,650 --> 00:23:04,400
So...

367
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,700
that's what you want...

368
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,870
Ow, ow, ow...

369
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:17,830
My ship's a wreck...

370
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:20,380
so I want a new one.

371
00:23:20,750 --> 00:23:24,800
I'll let you off the ship after
you've helped me with a few things.

372
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,220
Wh-What?!

373
00:23:26,220 --> 00:23:30,100
Don Krieg, this isn't
what you promised.

374
00:23:32,770 --> 00:23:36,730
I only have 100 underlings
left breathing on my ship.

375
00:23:37,190 --> 00:23:39,940
They're starving and severely injured.

376
00:23:40,820 --> 00:23:46,240
First, prepare 100 meals for them
along with some drinking water.

377
00:23:46,570 --> 00:23:48,910
Some have already starved to death.

378
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,830
W-Water...

379
00:23:56,250 --> 00:23:58,040
There's no time to waste!

380
00:23:58,830 --> 00:24:01,460
You want us to help pirates

381
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:03,880
that are gonna attack this ship?!

382
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:05,220
We refuse!

383
00:24:06,050 --> 00:24:07,720
Refuse?

384
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:09,640
Don't get the wrong idea.

385
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:12,310
I'm not placing an order.

386
00:24:12,310 --> 00:24:14,350
I'm giving you an order.

387
00:24:14,350 --> 00:24:15,850
I don't care who you are...

388
00:24:15,850 --> 00:24:21,980
don't you dare defy me!

389
00:24:26,950 --> 00:24:28,610
Sanji...

390
00:24:29,490 --> 00:24:31,740
Sanji, I'm sorry...

391
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:34,330
I didn't mean for this to happen...

392
00:24:34,330 --> 00:24:38,330
You son of a bitch!
You got us into this mess!

393
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:59,190
Hey, Sanji! Where are you going?!

394
00:25:01,150 --> 00:25:02,520
To the kitchen.

395
00:25:03,020 --> 00:25:06,150
I have to prepare another 100 meals.

396
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:07,650
Sanji!

397
00:25:07,650 --> 00:25:08,650
Sanji?!

398
00:25:08,650 --> 00:25:11,110
– What?!
– What?!

399
00:25:11,910 --> 00:25:13,200
Right.

400
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,830
That's how it should be.

401
00:25:19,620 --> 00:25:22,500
Are you working for Krieg, Sanji?!

402
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:24,590
We can't let you into the kitchen!

403
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:28,090
We're fed up with
your crazy behavior!

404
00:25:29,590 --> 00:25:31,050
Go ahead.

405
00:25:32,390 --> 00:25:34,470
If you want to stop me, go ahead!

406
00:25:37,470 --> 00:25:39,390
I know...

407
00:25:39,770 --> 00:25:43,860
He's an irredeemable villain.
I know that much.

408
00:25:46,110 --> 00:25:48,740
But that doesn't matter to me.

409
00:25:49,740 --> 00:25:51,820
Not one bit!

410
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:54,530
What happens after we feed them...

411
00:25:54,530 --> 00:25:56,530
I don't care about that.

412
00:25:56,530 --> 00:25:57,700
I'm a cook.

413
00:25:57,700 --> 00:26:00,040
No more. No less.

414
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:03,040
If someone's hungry, I'll feed them.

415
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:04,540
That's all there is to it.

416
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:07,210
Isn't a cook like that...

417
00:26:07,210 --> 00:26:09,420
perfectly acceptable?

418
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:18,520
Patty!

419
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:20,350
Hey, someone restrain him!

420
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:27,360
Sanji, you sometimes feed customers
I kick out the back door, right?

421
00:26:27,860 --> 00:26:33,320
I dunno who's right on that,
but this time, you're wrong.

422
00:26:33,780 --> 00:26:36,620
I won't let you keep doing
whatever you want.

423
00:26:36,620 --> 00:26:38,740
I'll protect this restaurant.

424
00:26:38,740 --> 00:26:40,620
Luckily, we only have
one man to beat.

425
00:26:40,620 --> 00:26:44,210
Even if he's Don Krieg,
what can he do against us?

426
00:26:46,460 --> 00:26:49,920
We deal with pirates here every day.

427
00:26:50,380 --> 00:26:53,680
We know how to serve
every type of customer!

428
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:54,840
That's...

429
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:58,470
Did you clear your plate, Krieg?

430
00:26:58,470 --> 00:27:00,770
After the main course, how about...

431
00:27:01,470 --> 00:27:05,900
a dessert of hot lead?!

432
00:27:06,650 --> 00:27:10,530
Tainted Meatball!

433
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:27,540
Don!

434
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:35,010
I think I broke the door.

435
00:27:35,010 --> 00:27:37,010
Chef Zeff's gonna yell at me again.

436
00:27:37,010 --> 00:27:39,260
Well, you did it
to protect the restaurant.

437
00:27:39,260 --> 00:27:40,890
It's a small price to pay.

438
00:27:41,470 --> 00:27:44,980
Any idea what to do about those
still aboard Krieg's ship?

439
00:27:44,980 --> 00:27:46,230
Lemme think...

440
00:27:46,230 --> 00:27:49,310
Maybe we'll spread butter
on the ship and stir-fry it.

441
00:27:49,650 --> 00:27:53,610
That sounds delicious...

442
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:55,820
you lame cook!

443
00:27:57,910 --> 00:28:00,330
How dare you serve me
such a nasty dessert?!

444
00:28:00,330 --> 00:28:02,790
This restaurant is the worst!

445
00:28:07,370 --> 00:28:09,670
You're damn annoying!

446
00:28:16,010 --> 00:28:17,430
From all over his body...

447
00:28:17,430 --> 00:28:18,550
Bullets...

448
00:28:32,770 --> 00:28:35,650
Don't you dare defy me!

449
00:28:36,150 --> 00:28:38,860
I'm the mightiest of them all!

450
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:42,370
Steel arms more powerful than flesh...

451
00:28:42,740 --> 00:28:45,500
A carapace made of
the strongest wootz steel...

452
00:28:45,500 --> 00:28:49,330
And diamond fists
to destroy anything!

453
00:28:50,420 --> 00:28:52,960
I have an array of weapons
hidden all over my body!

454
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:55,090
I command 50 ships...

455
00:28:55,090 --> 00:28:57,090
and 5,000 pirates!

456
00:28:57,090 --> 00:29:00,840
I've never lost a battle in my life!

457
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:05,390
I am the man worthy
of the title of don!

458
00:29:06,140 --> 00:29:08,140
Out of my way, kid!

459
00:29:10,310 --> 00:29:15,530
When I tell you to prepare food,
you shut up and do it!

460
00:29:15,980 --> 00:29:18,320
No one defies me!

461
00:29:21,570 --> 00:29:23,950
There's food for 100 in here.

462
00:29:23,950 --> 00:29:26,080
Take it straight to your ship.

463
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:27,540
– Head Chef Zeff!
– Head Chef Zeff!

464
00:29:29,710 --> 00:29:33,080
Z... Zeff?

465
00:29:37,300 --> 00:29:39,920
What the...? What do you
think you're doing?!

466
00:29:40,510 --> 00:29:45,600
If we revive the pirates on that ship,
they'll take over the entire restaurant!

467
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:49,480
That's only if they have
the will to fight.

468
00:29:51,190 --> 00:29:54,940
Isn't that right,
you Grand Line washout?

469
00:29:57,900 --> 00:29:59,650
N-No way.

470
00:29:59,650 --> 00:30:02,240
Don Krieg failed on the Grand Line?

471
00:30:02,610 --> 00:30:05,620
Even the conqueror of the East Blue...

472
00:30:05,620 --> 00:30:09,910
couldn't make it with
a fleet of fifty pirate ships?!

473
00:30:10,250 --> 00:30:11,870
The Grand Line?

474
00:30:11,870 --> 00:30:15,670
You... You're...

475
00:30:15,670 --> 00:30:17,590
Red Leg Zeff.

